"Sane One"

'''Alyssa''' (pronounced ah-LISS-ah) is a female given name of Greek origin. Some of its meanings are noble, of good cheer, wise, logical, rational. The name also means of princess, according to some writings.

The name is derived from the white, lavender, or bright yellow Alyssum flower.

There are many variant forms for Alyssa, including: Aly, Ally, Alissa, Alisse, Allissa, Allyse, Allyssa, Alysa, Alisa, Alyse, Alysse, Alyssia, Elisa, Elissa, Ellisa, Illissa, Ilisa, Illisa, Ilyssa, Ilysa, Lissy, Lissa, Lissie and Lyssa.